[{'language': 'eng', 'definition_type': 'informal', 'definition': 'predicate to conjunction: turns the following binary predicate into a logical conjunction; terminator: "ga".', 'notes': [], 'gloss': '', 'keywords': ''}, {'language': 'toa', 'definition_type': 'meta', 'definition': '[JIOI] Tu củaqmūıbō bı lủcōetōa lú sỉemē hóa shú jıoı cúaqmūıbō shú ga, kıo dàı sa rảı bı pảqnūa há shú ga kı, ceı müıbō hóa pó cúaqmūıbō da.

• ①̉   jıoı  ②̉  ga  ③̉   =  ②̉  ①̂  na  ③̂ .
• ①̉   ②́   na jıoı  ③̉  ga  ④̉  ⑤́   =  ③̉   ①̂  ②́   na  ④̂  ⑤́ .
• ①̉   ②̃  jıoı  ③̉   (ga)  ④̃  =  ③̉   ②̂   ①̂  na na  ④̂  ①̂ .', 'notes': [], 'gloss': '', 'keywords': ''}]

Compare ``chỏq jí ní jẽaq dảqfāı`` —"I use this increasingly frequently"— with ``chỏq meq pủıjēaq ní`` —"increasingly many ones use this"—.'), ('date', '2020-01-14T17:13:28.836Z'), ('author', 'Ilmen')]), OrderedDict([('content', 'What can be expressed as ``gủaı meq dùq póq`` under the alternative definition #46CV57Aje can be expressed as per this very definition as ``gủaı póq ru meq hỏpā dủq``, which is three syllables more. Hopefully the additional flexibility allowed by this one definition is a sufficient compensation.'), ('date', '2020-01-14T17:13:41.081Z'), ('author', 'Ilmen')])]
